1
00:00:03,170 --> 00:00:07,820
Now we want to understand routing in an MVC application.

2
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:15,080
Routing basically defines that in the URL when you type something where it should send that request

3
00:00:15,080 --> 00:00:15,450
to.

4
00:00:16,129 --> 00:00:23,000
We have configured a default route here, but when it comes to an MVC application, we have a certain

5
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:23,720
pattern.

6
00:00:24,260 --> 00:00:30,590
And before I show you that in the application, let me walk you through a presentation here to give

7
00:00:30,590 --> 00:00:32,030
you a rough idea.

8
00:00:32,930 --> 00:00:40,580
You can see the URL pattern for routing is considered after the domain name localhost, and port number

9
00:00:40,580 --> 00:00:42,020
is the domain name.

10
00:00:43,090 --> 00:00:49,300
This localhost can be google.com, can be .net mastery.com or whatever you want.

11
00:00:49,570 --> 00:00:57,040
When we have to consider routing, we remove that piece and anything after that is considered the routing

12
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:57,820
pattern.

13
00:00:58,530 --> 00:01:00,450
In an MVC application.

14
00:01:00,450 --> 00:01:04,890
The typical route that we have is a controller and then action.

15
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:11,100
Those are the two words that you should always, always remember and write it down.

16
00:01:11,370 --> 00:01:16,260
There is a controller and inside controller there are action methods.

17
00:01:17,020 --> 00:01:19,540
Let me show you that with an example here.

18
00:01:19,660 --> 00:01:26,290
In this first URL, you see we have the domain name, which is localhost, and then we have something

19
00:01:26,290 --> 00:01:32,230
called as forward slash category, forward slash index, and then a number three.

20
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:40,010
So the first thing that you see after the domain is the controller name and next thing with a forward

21
00:01:40,010 --> 00:01:42,710
slash will be an action name.

22
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:47,520
After that, if there is anything there that will be the ID.

23
00:01:48,540 --> 00:01:53,360
ID is an optional field that we already saw right here.

24
00:01:53,370 --> 00:01:55,710
You can see that is question mark.

25
00:01:56,510 --> 00:02:00,770
So if we go back, what is the first thing after the domain name?

26
00:02:00,770 --> 00:02:02,490
That is the category.

27
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:04,460
After that, we have index.

28
00:02:04,460 --> 00:02:11,930
And then if there is anything present that will be populated in the ID, that is the default pattern

29
00:02:11,930 --> 00:02:14,630
that has been defined in the .net project.

30
00:02:15,020 --> 00:02:20,510
Now, of course, we can modify some things here and we will do that in the later videos.

31
00:02:20,510 --> 00:02:22,910
But this is the default pattern.

32
00:02:23,150 --> 00:02:28,340
We have controllers and inside there we have action based on that.

33
00:02:28,340 --> 00:02:35,180
I have an example here and I want you to find out that based on the URL, what will be the category

34
00:02:35,180 --> 00:02:39,650
and what will be the action and if there is an ID or not.

35
00:02:41,420 --> 00:02:46,860
The first example here category is the controller and index is the action.

36
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:50,600
We do not have any ID, so ID will be null.

37
00:02:51,710 --> 00:02:55,190
After that we only have something called as category.

38
00:02:55,730 --> 00:03:01,670
If there is no action defined, then by default the action will be index action.

39
00:03:02,060 --> 00:03:05,560
We do not have any action defined in the second example.

40
00:03:05,570 --> 00:03:08,310
So controller will be category.

41
00:03:08,330 --> 00:03:11,960
Action will be index and ID will be null.

42
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:20,800
In the third example here we have controller name as category action name as edit, and then we have

43
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,950
some ID with the value of three.

44
00:03:24,990 --> 00:03:29,790
And the final example here we have a controller with the name of product.

45
00:03:29,820 --> 00:03:35,520
We have an action with the name of details and ID with a value of three.

46
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:40,260
Now you might be wondering what is the importance of this assignment?

47
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:44,620
Well, it is really important from now onwards.

48
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:52,170
If you look at a URL that is using MVC architecture, you can tell what is the controller name and what

49
00:03:52,170 --> 00:03:53,430
is the action name.

50
00:03:53,880 --> 00:04:00,450
Now, if I go back here, we are saying that the default controller is home and action is index.

51
00:04:00,570 --> 00:04:07,170
That basically means that if nothing is defined after the domain name, it is telling the application

52
00:04:07,170 --> 00:04:11,760
that you should go to home controller and index action method.

53
00:04:12,490 --> 00:04:18,310
That is the default route that .net team has configured in Program.cs.

54
00:04:18,670 --> 00:04:25,030
If you want, you can change that default route, but that is the default route and you know how that

55
00:04:25,030 --> 00:04:28,810
will be converted to a URL if you want.

56
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:30,670
Now enough talking.

57
00:04:30,700 --> 00:04:35,140
Let me show you routing in action in the next video.

